ts test.","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"Tm33EFPfbm"}],"key":"UibKCKCWGI"}],"key":"w5VZnpS7S1"}],"label":"fig:combinedenvironmentselector","identifier":"fig:combinedenvironmentselector","enumerator":"16.1","html_id":"fig-combinedenvironmentselector","key":"KDQ2J2AKnc"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Combined environments tests have the potential to be very complex, as parameters for multiple environments need to be defined.  To make the setup of combined environments tests less tedious, Rattlesnake gives the user an option to load a combined environments profile using the ","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"key":"jI3K42UJ7o"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Load Profile...","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"key":"pTfCFSa2D7"},{"type":"text","value":" button.  This profile is an Excel workbook with multiple worksheets defining the channel setup, global data acquisition parameters, environment parameters, as well as the test timeline.  Rattlesnake allows the user to save a profile template to disk, which can be opened and modified to specify the entire combined environments test by clicking the ","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"key":"iSX0SkqE45"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Save Profile Template...","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"key":"M2jtpi9n8p"},{"type":"text","value":" button.  Note that the template will be created with placeholder environments corresponding to the environments that are displayed in the Environment table, so it is in the user’s best interest to add the required environments to the table using the ","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"key":"NG2FEyE7dU"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Add Environment","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"key":"xXBu70QeV3"},{"type":"text","value":" button and define each environment’s type and name prior to saving the template.","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"key":"iemPwuUMcD"}],"key":"HwibMMEuSG"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once the environments in the combined environments test are selected, the ","key":"L6NGlxyLK9"},{"type":"abbreviation","title":"Graphical User Interface","children":[{"type":"text","value":"GUI","key":"l4rxmh4Jas"}],"key":"a7aZCI0xNj"},{"type":"text","value":" is set up accordingly.  Users will notice the addition of an ","key":"QWzOoNbbPe"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Environment Table","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"bWBbKLu9ay"},{"type":"text","value":" on the ","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"bSZgUfPj20"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Data Acquisition Setup","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"BAyoXjQS9m"},{"type":"text","value":" tab which can be used to determine which excitation and response channels are to be used by each environment.  Excitation signals can be used by one or more environments.  If an excitation signal is used by multiple environments that will be run simultaneously, the excitation signal output to the hardware will end up being a summation of the individual environment’s output signals.  It is up to the user to ensure that the combination of environment signals does not exceed the output that the hardware is capable of.  Similarly, response signals can be used by single environments, multiple environments, or no environments.  Only response signals belonging to a specific environment will be passed to that environment for analysis.  Note however that the part may be responding to excitation from multiple environments, so even if a given channel is only used by one environment, it may have response contributions from all active environments.  It is up to the user to design each environment such that this “cross-talk” is handled correctly, Rattlesnake will not attempt to separate a given response into contributions from each environment.  If a signal is used by no environments, it will still be recorded and saved to disk; however, data from it will not be delivered to any environment.","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"vT6AApIPdq"}],"key":"Zbtz6TUKJO"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"With multiple environments defined, the ","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"aEeHPw05cp"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Environment Definition","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"LBXjzDPv4w"},{"type":"text","value":" and ","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"NgzFIl0xQi"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Run Test","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"dEVaIoaHn1"},{"type":"text","value":" tabs will have a sub-tab to define or control each environment.  On the ","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"OmcoVPlPlP"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Environment Definition","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"K7KDWbcH6k"},{"type":"text","value":" tab, each environment’s sub-tab will need to be defined prior to selecting the ","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"axf8OVRxAF"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Initialize Environments","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"orxYCG4yAa"},{"type":